# Environment Configuration Guide

This file shows you how to configure the application for different environments.

## Local Development (Default)
```
REACT_APP_API_URL=http://localhost:5000/api
```

## Ngrok Testing
1. Start ngrok for backend: `ngrok http 5000`
2. Copy the ngrok URL (e.g., `https://abc123.ngrok.io`)
3. Update `.env`:
```
REACT_APP_API_URL=https://abc123.ngrok.io/api
```
4. Restart React app: `npm start`

## Production Deployment
Update `.env` with your production backend URL:
```
REACT_APP_API_URL=https://api.yourdomain.com/api
```

**Important:** After changing `.env`, you must restart the React development server (`npm start`) for changes to take effect.
